# Short commits

When the user asks to commit, or you draft a commit message for this repo, **always use a short message**. Do not write paragraph-length subjects or multi-sentence bodies by default.

## Format

- `type(scope): imperative summary` — scope optional
- Types: `feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `perf`, `docs`, `test`, `chore`, `build`, `ci`, `style`, `revert`
- Imperative mood: `add`, `fix`, `remove` — not `added` / `adding`
- **Subject ≤50 characters** when possible (hard cap 72)
- No trailing period on the subject

## Body

- **Omit the body** when the subject is self-explanatory (most commits)
- Add a body **only** for breaking changes, security fixes, or data migrations

## Examples

✅ `refactor(setup): tighten toolbar layout`

❌ `Refactor CSS styles for setup toolbar components to improve layout and responsiveness...`
